{
  "title": "Maxon Cinema 4D Import-Export Pro",
  "coverImage": "",
  "galleryImages": [],
  "description": "<div style=\"width:800px;max-width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;font-family:-apple-system , BlinkMacSystemFont , 'Segoe UI' , Roboto , Helvetica , Arial , sans-serif;background-color:#ffffff;\">    <table width=\"100%\" style=\"text-align:center;background-color:rgb(255, 255, 255);border:1px solid rgb(229, 231, 235);border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;\">        <tbody>\n<tr>      <td style=\"padding:28px 28px 22px 28px;background-color:#0b1020;background-image:linear-gradient(135deg,#0b1020 0%,#111b35 60%,#0b1020 100%);\">        <div style=\"font-size:30px;font-weight:750;color:#f8fafc;line-height:1.18;margin:0 0 10px 0;\">          🚀 <span style=\"color:#ffffff;\">Maxon Cinema 4D Import-Export Pro</span>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.78);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.6;\">          The fastest way to import Cinema 4D projects into Blender！        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.86);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.75;\">          A polished, production-ready addon that imports selected          <code style=\"background-color:rgba(248,250,252,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(248,250,252,0.14);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:6px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;color:#f8fafc;\">.c4d</code>          project files directly from Blender—no need to keep Cinema 4D open. It preserves core assets with minimal friction:        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:rgba(255,183,77,0.95);margin:0 0 0 0;line-height:1.75;padding:12px 16px;background-color:rgba(255,183,77,0.15);border:1px solid rgba(255,183,77,0.4);border-radius:8px;\">          <div style=\"font-weight:600;color:#ffb74d;margin-bottom:8px;\">Pro Features: Support for importing advanced Cinema 4D features</div>          <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:0;\">            <tbody>\n<tr>              <td style=\"padding:0 12px 0 8px;vertical-align:top;width:50%;\">                <div style=\"font-size:12px;line-height:1.8;color:rgba(255,183,77,0.95);\">                  <div style=\"margin-bottom:4px;\">• <strong style=\"color:#ffb74d;\">XPresso</strong> – Cinema 4D's node-based programming system</div>                  <div style=\"margin-bottom:4px;\">• <strong style=\"color:#ffb74d;\">Cloner</strong> – MoGraph cloner objects and instances</div>                  <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">• <strong style=\"color:#ffb74d;\">Effectors</strong> – MoGraph effector system (random, delay, formula, etc.)</div>                </div>              </td>              <td style=\"padding:0 8px 0 12px;vertical-align:top;width:50%;\">                <div style=\"font-size:12px;line-height:1.8;color:rgba(255,183,77,0.95);\">                  <div style=\"margin-bottom:4px;\">• <strong style=\"color:#ffb74d;\">Matrix Animation</strong> – MoGraph matrix modes and animation</div>                  <div style=\"margin-bottom:4px;\">• <strong style=\"color:#ffb74d;\">Dynamics</strong> – Rigid body, soft body, and cloth simulation</div>                  <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">• <strong style=\"color:#ffb74d;\">Fields</strong> – Field system and force field control</div>                </div>              </td>            </tr>          </tbody>\n</table>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;height:0;overflow:hidden;border-radius:8px;\">          <div class=\"ratio ratio-16x9\"><iframe frameborder=\"0\" src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/I0cZkvQ-NHI\" style=\"position:absolute;top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;\" allowfullscreen=\"\"></iframe></div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Overview</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Overview</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          Bring Cinema 4D scenes straight into Blender—and send them back—without juggling extra software or manual conversions. Import-Export Pro appears in Blender's file menu, letting you open, edit, and re-save native <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">.c4d</strong> projects while preserving geometry, materials, animations, cameras, lights, splines, hierarchy, and scale. Perfect for studios that need quick turn-around, freelancers who switch between tools, and educators who want the simplest pipeline possible.        </div>        <div style=\"margin:14px 0;\">          <img src=\"https://assets.superhivemarket.com/cache/84676f7474117508d7d2b390f60c0115.gif\" style=\"max-width:100%;border-radius:8px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;\">        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Features</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Key Benefits</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:0;border-collapse:collapse;\">          <tbody>\n<tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;width:30%;\">Bidirectional</td>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Open .c4d files inside Blender and export Blender scenes back to .c4d from the same panel.</td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Full-Fidelity Transfer</td>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Meshes, materials & textures, UVs, bones, shape keys, lights, cameras, splines, keyframes—nothing lost.</td>          </tr>          <tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Two Conversion Modes</td>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">\n<em>Precision Mode</em> for pixel-accurate assets, <em>Fast Mode</em> for speedy iterations. Switch anytime.</td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Smart Scaling</td>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Automatic unit matching keeps dimensions consistent between both DCCs.</td>          </tr>          <tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Custom Cache & Logging</td>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Choose where temporary files live and keep detailed logs for pipeline audits.</td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Cross-Platform</td>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Works on Windows, macOS, and Linux with Blender 3.6 LTS – 5.0+.</td>          </tr>          <tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">UI Shortcut</td>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Optional \"Import .c4d\" button in the 3D View header for drag-and-drop speed.</td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Localization Ready</td>            <td style=\"padding:12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">English & Simplified Chinese included; add more languages via one JSON.</td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Benefits</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Why Import-Export Pro?</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:12px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">No Extra Hassle</strong> – Skip juggling multiple converter apps or lengthy export chains.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:12px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Studio-Ready</strong> – Batch-convert asset libraries or plug it into automated build systems.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:12px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Future Proof</strong> – Lifetime updates, tested on Blender stable & alpha builds.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Fair Licensing</strong> – One seat covers unlimited personal or commercial projects; render nodes included (see EULA).          </div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Compatibility</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Compatibility</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Blender:</strong> 3.6 LTS – 5.0+          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">OS:</strong> Windows 10/11, macOS 13+, Linux (glibc 2.31+)          </div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Installation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Installation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">1. Download the <code style=\"background-color:#f1f5f9;padding:2px 6px;border-radius:4px;font-size:13px;font-family:'Courier New' , monospace;color:#0f172a;\">.zip</code> from the right-hand column.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">2. Blender → <em>Edit ▸ Preferences ▸ Add-ons ▸ Install</em> → select the zip → enable.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">3. You'll see <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Maxon Cinema 4D (.c4d)</strong> under <em>File ▸ Import/Export</em>—or simply drag a .c4d into the viewport.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">4. For exporting, choose <em>File ▸ Export ▸ Maxon Cinema 4D (.c4d)</em>.</div>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#64748b;font-style:italic;padding:10px 12px;background-color:#f8fafc;border-left:3px solid #d6a44a;border-radius:4px;margin:0;\">          A step-by-step PDF guide and video walkthrough are available in the Support tab.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Support</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Support & Updates</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • Email & ticket system (48 h response)          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • Community chat groups for real-time help          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">            • Built-in updater for future versions          </div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Updates</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Changelog (v 2.2.3)</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 20px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">• Supported Blender 5.0 version</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">• Fix known issues</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">• Fixed an error when exporting hidden objects</div>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">Changelog (v 2.1.8)</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">• New Linux batch converter option</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">• \"Skip Materials\" toggle for look-dev passes</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">• Performance boost: faster export in Precision Mode</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">• Fixed rare hierarchy mismatch on export</div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Community</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">🌱 Support Blender Foundation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0;\">          We believe in giving back to the community that makes our work possible. Every month, we dedicate a portion of our plugin's revenue to support the Blender Foundation. Thank you for helping us contribute to the future of open-source creativity.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Tags</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0;\">          c4d, blender, import-export, pipeline, 3d-tools, materials, animation        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:18px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#64748b;line-height:1.6;\">          © 2025 Maxon Cinema 4D Import‑Export Pro · blenderVfxMaster        </div>      </td>    </tr>  </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>",
  "documentation": "<div style=\"width:800px;max-width:100%;margin:0 auto;padding:24px;font-family:-apple-system , BlinkMacSystemFont , 'Segoe UI' , Roboto , Helvetica , Arial , sans-serif;background-color:#ffffff;\">    <table width=\"100%\" style=\"background-color:#ffffff;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;border-radius:14px;overflow:hidden;\">        <tbody>\n<tr>      <td style=\"padding:28px 28px 22px 28px;background-color:#0b1020;background-image:linear-gradient(135deg,#0b1020 0%,#111b35 60%,#0b1020 100%);\">        <div style=\"font-size:30px;font-weight:750;color:#f8fafc;line-height:1.18;margin:0 0 10px 0;\">          🚀 <span style=\"color:#ffffff;\">Maxon Cinema 4D Import‑Export Pro Document</span>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.78);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.6;\">          The fastest way to import Cinema 4D projects into Blender！        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:rgba(248,250,252,0.86);margin:0 0 14px 0;line-height:1.75;\">          A polished, production-ready addon that imports selected          <code style=\"background-color:rgba(248,250,252,0.10);border:1px solid rgba(248,250,252,0.14);padding:2px 6px;border-radius:6px;font-family:ui-monospace , SFMono-Regular , Menlo , Monaco , Consolas , monospace;color:#f8fafc;\">.c4d</code>          project files directly from Blender—no need to keep Cinema 4D open. It preserves core assets with minimal friction:        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\"><br></div>\n<div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Overview</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">1. What is it?</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Maxon Cinema 4D Import‑Export Pro</strong> lets you open, edit, and save native .c4d scenes directly inside Blender. Geometry, materials, animations, lights, cameras, and splines travel both ways with a single click, so you can keep Cinema 4D assets in your pipeline without ever launching Cinema 4D.        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0;\">          Perfect for studios migrating to Blender, freelancers who receive C4D files, and anyone who juggles multi‑DCC projects.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Features</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">2. Key Features</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Bidirectional Support</strong> – Import and export .c4d files from the File ▶ Import‑Export menu.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Dual Conversion Modes</strong>            <div style=\"margin-left:20px;margin-top:4px;\">              - <strong>Precise</strong> (Alembic‑based) for maximum fidelity.<br>              - <strong>Standard</strong> (FBX‑based) for blazing speed.            </div>          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Component Toggles</strong> – Choose exactly which elements to include: models, lights, cameras, splines, animations, materials.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Drag‑and‑Drop</strong> – Drop any .c4d file into the 3D Viewport and get an options popup.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">One‑Tap Toolbar Button</strong> – Optional import icon in the 3D View header for even faster access.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Frame‑Range Import</strong> – Bring in only the animation segment you need (Precise mode).          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Custom Cache & Robust Logging</strong> – Set your own temporary directory and review a detailed log at any time.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Cross‑Platform</strong> – Windows 10/11, macOS 12+, and modern Linux distros.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Blender 4.2 LTS Ready</strong> – Fully tested with the latest Blender builds.          </div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Setup</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">3. Installation</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">1. Download the ZIP from BlenderMarket (do not unzip).</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">2. Inside Blender: Edit ▶ Preferences ▶ Add‑ons ▶ Install and select the ZIP.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">3. Enable the checkbox \"Maxon Cinema 4D Import‑Export Pro.\"</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">4. (Optional) Click the add‑on's ⚙︎ Preferences to:            <div style=\"margin-left:20px;margin-top:4px;\">              - Set a custom Cache Directory (SSD recommended for large scenes).<br>              - Show or hide the 3D View Import Button.<br>              - Pick default Import/Export Formats.            </div>          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">5. Save Preferences and restart Blender if prompted.</div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Getting Started</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">4. Quick Start</div>                <div style=\"font-size:15px;font-weight:650;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 6px 0;\">Importing a .c4d Scene:</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">1. File ▶ Import ▶ Maxon Cinema 4D (.c4d)</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">2. Choose Precise (Alembic) or Standard (FBX).</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">3. Toggle the scene elements you wish to import.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">4. (Precise mode) Specify a custom frame range if you only need part of the animation.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">5. Click Import — that's it!</div>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:15px;font-weight:650;color:#0f172a;margin:14px 0 6px 0;\">Exporting back to .c4d:</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">1. File ▶ Export ▶ Maxon Cinema 4D (.c4d)</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">2. Select the objects you want to send.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:6px;\">3. Pick Precise or Standard and the components to include.</div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">4. Press Export and choose a destination.</div>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#64748b;font-style:italic;padding:10px 12px;background-color:#f8fafc;border-left:3px solid #d6a44a;border-radius:4px;margin:0;\">          <strong>Tip:</strong> You can mix‑and‑match modes. For example, use fast Standard imports for look‑dev, then switch to Precise for final animation hand‑off.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Workflows</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">5. Advanced Workflows</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:0;border-collapse:collapse;\">          <tbody>\n<tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Need to…</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Try this</td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#0f172a;font-weight:500;\">Keep file sizes small</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Disable Materials on export and re‑apply Blender shaders later</td>          </tr>          <tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#0f172a;font-weight:500;\">Sync only cameras</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Un‑check everything except Cameras</td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#0f172a;font-weight:500;\">Preview a single shot</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Use Precise mode + custom frame range</td>          </tr>          <tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#0f172a;font-weight:500;\">Batch convert many files</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Drag multiple .c4d files into the viewport; each will open with its own popup</td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Compatibility</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">6. Compatibility</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Blender:</strong> 4.2 LTS or newer (works on Alpha & Beta builds too).          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">File Types:</strong> Native .c4d saves from R21 and above.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">OS:</strong> Windows, macOS (Apple Silicon & Intel), Linux (glibc 2.35+).          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">            • <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Unit Scale:</strong> 1 Cinema 4D unit = 1 cm. The add‑on handles scale adjustments automatically.          </div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Limitations</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">7. Known Limitations</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • Procedural or third‑party Cinema 4D shaders may import as baked textures.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • MoGraph effectors and X‑Particles are currently baked to geometry.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            • Very large scenes (10 M+ polygons) may require the Precise mode and an SSD cache for best stability.          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">            We continuously improve coverage—join the community group below to vote for next‑priority features.          </div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Support</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">8. Troubleshooting & Support</div>        <table width=\"100%\" style=\"margin:0 0 14px 0;border-collapse:collapse;\">          <tbody>\n<tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Symptom</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;color:#0f172a;\">Solution</td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#0f172a;font-weight:500;\">Import/export fails instantly</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Verify the Cache Directory has write permission and enough disk space.</td>          </tr>          <tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#0f172a;font-weight:500;\">Nothing appears after import</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Make sure the object types you need (e.g. Models) were enabled in the popup.</td>          </tr>          <tr>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#0f172a;font-weight:500;\">Animation starts at wrong frame</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">Use the Frame Range option or set your Blender scene's start frame to match.</td>          </tr>          <tr style=\"background-color:#f8fafc;\">            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#0f172a;font-weight:500;\">Need more help</td>            <td style=\"padding:10px 12px;border:1px solid #e5e7eb;font-size:14px;color:#475569;\">1) Check the detailed log at Documents/blender_c4d_log.txt 2) Visit our Issue Tracker or QQ support group.</td>          </tr>        </tbody>\n</table>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Documentation:</strong> <a href=\"https://space.bilibili.com/34368968\" style=\"color:#2563eb;text-decoration:underline;\">https://space.bilibili.com/34368968</a>          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:8px;\">            <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Issue Tracker:</strong> <a href=\"https://github.com/475519905/blender-Import-export-cinema4d-file\" style=\"color:#2563eb;text-decoration:underline;\">https://github.com/475519905/blender-Import-export-cinema4d-file</a>          </div>          <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">            <strong style=\"color:#0f172a;\">Community:</strong> QQ Group ID in the add‑on Preferences.          </div>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">License</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">9. Licensing</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0;\">          A purchase grants one seat for commercial or personal use. Minor updates within the 2.x cycle are free. For studio licensing or special builds, please contact us.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:#16a34a;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Updates</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#0f172a;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">10. Changelog (excerpt)</div>        <div style=\"border-left:3px solid #ffb74d;padding-left:14px;margin-bottom:14px;\">          <div style=\"font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#ff701b;margin-bottom:8px;\">v2.1.8</div>          <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:#475569;line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 8px 0;\">            <div style=\"margin-bottom:4px;\">• Added drag‑and‑drop importer with settings popup.</div>            <div style=\"margin-bottom:4px;\">• New 3D View toolbar icon.</div>            <div style=\"margin-bottom:4px;\">• Separate defaults for import and export formats.</div>            <div style=\"margin-bottom:0;\">• Performance optimizations for heavy Alembic streams.</div>          </div>        </div>        <div style=\"font-size:13px;color:#64748b;margin:0;\">          Full history available in the documentation.        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:26px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#5865f2;background-image:linear-gradient(135deg,#5865f2 0%,#4752c4 100%);\">        <div style=\"font-size:11px;letter-spacing:1.2px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.9);margin:0 0 8px 0;\">Community</div>        <div style=\"font-size:24px;font-weight:750;color:#ffffff;margin:0 0 14px 0;\">💬 Join Discord Community</div>        <div style=\"font-size:14px;color:rgba(255,255,255,0.95);line-height:1.75;margin:0 0 16px 0;\">          Connect with other users, get support, share your work, and stay updated with the latest news and updates.        </div>        <div>          <a href=\"https://discord.gg/yVCfJjPYj7\" style=\"display:inline-block;padding:12px 24px;background-color:#ffffff;color:#5865f2;text-decoration:none;font-weight:700;font-size:14px;border-radius:8px;\">            Join Discord Server →          </a>        </div>      </td>    </tr>        <tr>      <td style=\"padding:18px 28px;border-top:1px solid #e5e7eb;background-color:#ffffff;\">        <div style=\"font-size:12px;color:#64748b;line-height:1.6;\">          © <span>2025</span> Maxon Cinema 4D Import‑Export Pro · blenderVfxMaster        </div>      </td>    </tr>  </tbody>\n</table>\n</div>",
